This paper deals with generating 3D shapes from 2D images, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The method also involves training a generative adversarial network (GAN), which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of view prediction networks, which are commonly used in graphics (cs.GR). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of weakly supervised learning, which is a topic in both computer vision and machine learning (cs.CV, cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the multi-projection GAN to learn high-dimensional distributions from lower dimensional training datasets, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
